  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7014.47 sitting just above the max negative gamma strike at 7015, dealers are likely buying the dip here as they're short gamma at this level. The massive positive gamma wall at 7000 (9670.9M) creates strong support where dealers will aggressively sell any bounce, while the PIN regime suggests mean reversion back toward that 7000 level. Watch for rejection at the 7050 gamma wall (9328.0M) on any relief rally, as dealers will be heavy sellers into that strength.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect a grind back down toward 7000 with limited upside past 7050.",
